quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  2,8,"And from the people who say: \"We believed by God and with the Day the Last/ Resurrection Day.\" And they are not with believing"
  2,9,"They deceive God, and those who believed, and they do not deceive except themselves, and they do not feel/know/sense"
  2,10,"In their hearts/minds (is) sickness/disease, so God increased them sickness/disease, and for them (is a) painful torture because (of) what they were lying/denying/falsifying"
  2,11,"And if (it was) said to them: \"Do not corrupt in the earth/Planet Earth.\" They said: \"But we are correcting/repairing"
  2,12,"Is it not that they truly are, they are the corrupting and but they do not feel/know/sense"
  2,13,"And if (it was/is) said to them: \"Believe as the people believed.\" They said: \"Do we believe as the ignorant/foolish believed?\" Is it not that they truly are, they are the ignorant/foolish and but they do not know"
  2,14,"And if they met/found those who believed, they said: \"We believed\". And if they were alone/together with to their devils they said: \"That we are with you, but we are mocking"
  2,15,God moc ks with (about) them and extends/spreads them in their tyranny (being) confused/puzzled
  2,16,"Those are those who bought/volunteered the misguidance with the guidance, so their commercial trade/buying and selling did not profit/gain, and they were not guided"
  2,17,"Their example (is) as the one who ignited a fire, so when it lit/illuminated what (is) around/surrounding him, God took/went away with their light, and left them in darknesses, they do not see/understand"
  2,18,"Deaf, mute, blind , so they do not return"
  2,19,"Or as a rain from the sky, in it (is) darknesses and thunder and lightning, they put their fingers intheir ears from the thunderous noise , fearing the death , and God (is) with the disbelievers surrounding/enveloping"
  2,20,"The lightning almost snatches their eye sights , whenever (it) lit for them they walked in it, and if (it) darkened on them they stood and if God willed/wanted, He would have gone/taken away with their hearing/sense of hearing , and their sights/understanding , that God (is) on every thing capable/powerful"